The paper presents a method that uses deep convolutional neural networks and conditional random fields for depth estimation and topographical reconstruction from conventional endoscopy images. This involves computer vision and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the computer science sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the development of an endoscope camera model and rendering of anatomically-realistic colon images, which could fall under the computer graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper also involves the use of medical imaging techniques, which could fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
